        "## 6. Time-Series Transformations \n",
        "### ✅ Compute simple monthly returns\n",
        "### ✅ Wealth index\n",
        "### ✅ Rolling averages/volatility\n",
        "### ✅ Correlations between assets\n",
        "\n",
        "These operations are used everywhere in finance, investment operations, and risk analysis."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "9329f953",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Returns for A and B\n",
        "returnsA = dfA.pct_change().dropna()\n",
        "returnsB = dfB.pct_change().dropna()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Wealth index\n",
        "wealthA = (1 + returnsA['PriceA']).cumprod()\n",
        "wealthA.head()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "7212ca17",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 7. Merging / Joining Multiple DataFrames\n",
        "Merging/joining datasets is crucial when combining sleeves, markets, or indicators.\n",
        "\n",
        "### ✅ Try these joins:\n",
        "- `inner` join\n",
        "- `outer` join (shows missing dates if any)\n",
        "- `left` join\n",
        "\n",
        "Explain in markdown what difference you observed."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "ba1efdf7",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "combined = dfA.join(dfB, how='inner')\n",
        "combined.head()"
      ]
    },
