      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "2dafc631",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 8. Vectorisation vs Loops\n",
        "Vectorised operations in pandas/numpy are *much faster* than Python loops.\n",
        "This matters in finance where datasets can be millions of rows.\n",
        "\n",
        "### ✅ Compare performance, clarity, correctness."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "b970a134",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Loop version (slow)\n",
        "%%timeit\n",
        "out = []\n",
        "for r in returnsA['PriceA']:\n",
        "    out.append(r * 12)  # e.g., annualising monthly return (not exact)\n",
        "loop_res = pd.Series(out, index=returnsA.index)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "6776dc8d",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Vectorised version (fast)\n",
        "%%timeit\n",
        "vec_res = returnsA['PriceA'] * 12"
      ]
    },
